article.headline: Utah 54, Air Force 43
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. -- Marshall Henderson scored 16 points, and Utah held Air Force to a season-low points total in a 54-43 win on Wednesday night. Henderson scored in double figures for the 11th straight game. The Utes (13-14, 6-7 Mountain West) earned a sixth straight win against Air Force (9-17, 1-12), which has lost 12 of its last 13 contests. Grant Parker led the Falcons with 11 points, and Todd Fletcher added 10. Luka Drca added 13 points and Jay Watkins 10 for Utah.
